# Flink Jobs
jobs/*.jar

# metals (it is recommended to add .metals/ to .gitignore to avoid committing generated files from the Metals language server)
# metals languague server is used for Scala development, and it generates files in the .metals/ directory. These files are not meant to be committed to version control, as they can be regenerated by the language server when needed. By adding .metals/ to .gitignore, you can prevent these generated files from being accidentally committed to your repository, keeping it clean and focused on your source code.
.metals/

